Title: How to Take Smart Notes: One Simple Technique to Boost Writing, Learning and Thinking – for Students, Academics and Nonfiction Book Writers
Author: Sönke Ahrens
Private Notes: No longer a university student. I was recalling all the times my friends and I fell into a flow of discussion, all the thoughts that pass by unwritten, and just when you want to journal, how those thoughts and tangents never come back to you as they existed at first. While writing is an activity that emerges regularly in our lives, even converting abstract and overflowing thoughts into structured speech is a thing in itself... and I feel this "practice" of writing only makes that more natural over time.
